Building ION directly from source

Use the autogen script to prepare the build environment.

    ./autogen.sh
    ./configure
    make

Always verify the signatures and checksums.

If you want to install, run additionaly:

    make install

See doc/build-*.md for instructions on building iond,
the intended-for-services, no-graphical-interface, reference
implementation of ION.

Install with Ubuntu Software Center (Preffer and simple for most users)

    1. Open Ubuntu Software Center
    2. Search for ioncoin
    3. Install

Install with SNAP (Preffer and simple for most users)

    sudo snap install --edge ioncoin

    Available commands to run binaries

        - qt (GUI): ioncoin.qt
        - daemon: ioncoin.daemon
        - to run cli: ioncoin.cli
        - to run tx: ioncoin.tx

to upgrade/update ioncoin: snap refresh
if you run in on masternodes
then better install stable branch/version:
sudo snap install --stable ioncoin